<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the DocumentMetadata data structure — holds file-level metadata and supports dynamic attribute addition. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Document metadata: file info, timestamps, UID generation, extensible attributes. \par \b Input\/ \:  File name, temp name, size, timestamps, MIME type, optional UID, extra kwargs. \par \b Output\/ \:  DocumentMetadata instance with auto-generated or provided UID. \par \b Links\/ \:  [INHERITS(5): Serializable, USES_API(8): ApiDocumentMetadata] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>uid is always a non-empty string (auto-generated if not provided) \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why use **kwargs for extensibility? A: Different document formats have different metadata fields; kwargs enable format-specific extensions without schema changes. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Added semantic markup and LDD logging] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
